Add global configuration and safe Windows header; enhance face detection UI and management features
- Introduced `global_config.h` for UTF-8 execution character set and Windows-specific configurations. - Created `safe_windows.h` to manage Windows-specific macros and warnings. - Updated `win32tools.cpp` and `main.cpp` to include UTF-8 character set pragma. - Enhanced `FaceDetectWindow` with a new `FaceRecognitionWorker` class for asynchronous face recognition. - Implemented face management UI in `MainWindow` with options to register, view, and delete faces. - Improved error handling and logging for face registration and recognition processes. - Added functionality to save and load face databases, ensuring persistence across sessions. - Refactored face landmark saving to ensure safe file naming and character encoding. - Updated UI elements for better user experience and added help dialog with usage instructions.
